;s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTA8Et033JRedFwif767Aa0NxFX1FKRf5hCvQ";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:2448;s:6:"height";i:3264;s:6:"source";s:50:"https://www.baysidegaragedoor.com/repairs-service/";s:6:"domain";s:25:"www.baysidegaragedoor.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:61:{i:0;s:54:"You want to make sure that the tooth section faces in.";i:1;s:60:"Make sure that the belt is around the sprocket and is tight.";i:2;s:92:"Then make sure it stays put as you bring the opener back up to the bracket and reinstall it.";i:3;s:86:"These few guidelines should help you to get the garage door opener belt back on track.";i:4;s:135:"If you are are having trouble with your garage door opener belt running off track there are a few things that you need to do to fix it.";i:5;s:57:"Steps to fix garage door off track Disconnect the opener.";i:6;s:84:"To start the process check overhead for a rope that connects the opener to the door.";i:7;s:84:"Ensuring that the door is completely released from the opener lift the door to open.";i:8;s:118:"If youve noticed your garage door off track we have some tips to help you understand how to fix garage door off track.";i:9;s:69:"Gather materials needed for putting a garage door back on its tracks.";i:10;s:132:"These include a wrench hammer pliers wood blocks or sawhorses and some sort of lubricating substance like spray or even cooking oil.";i:11;s:126:"If there were a time when a car or other object hits the garage door it is possible that the rollers will come off the tracks.";i:12;s:82:"It may be only one or two of the rollers especially in the lower part of the door.";i:13;s:90:"If that is the case the rollers may cause the horizontal rails to bend under the pressure.";i:14;s:81:"All the moving parts of a garage door need to be aligned for it to work properly.";i:15;s:110:"If you notice that the rollers have jumped the track immediately stop using the door until it can be repaired.";i:16;s:121:"Continuing to use the door when the rollers are off track can cause serious damage to the tracks or even the door itself.";i:17;s:47:"Garage doors can go off track for many reasons.";i:18;s:67:"The door going off track is usually the symptom of another problem.";i:19;s:87:"For example a door can go off track if your torsion spring breaks or if a cable breaks.";i:20;s:133:"It could also go off track if it closes on some object and the safety reverse does not function correctly on your garage door opener.";i:21;s:242:"The key reason that causes the garage door rollers will come off-track from a single bad roller or many bad rollers is that if the door fails to roll-up and down correctly the opener will likely have difficulties opening and closing the door.";i:22;s:201:"Put in another way if the garage opener cannot open the door it could make the cables jump off from the cable drum and cause the garage door to be uneven and if the door becomes uneven the garage door.";i:23;s:38:"Garage door wheel off track - YouTube.";i:24;s:22:"ANGLE 61 ALLIE PHVID3.";i:25;s:60:"If playback doesnt begin shortly try restarting your device.";i:26;s:114:"If your garage door track is bent make sure to stop using it and replace the parts that are not working correctly.";i:27;s:95:"The most common components that fail in a garage track mechanism are the springs and the motor.";i:28;s:114:"Garage doors can resist for years without problems but they can only last long if given the necessary maintenance.";i:29;s:76:"Never force the door to go further because you could cause even more damage.";i:30;s:88:"Instead disengage the garage door opener by pulling on a rope in the center of the door.";i:31;s:34:"Identify the cause of the problem.";i:32;s:101:"The next step in the process of fixing the garage door off track is to find the cause of the problem.";i:33;s:69:"There could be a number of reasons why your garage door is off track.";i:34;s:62:"Check to see if the tracks are anchored to your garages walls.";i:35;s:116:"The tracks separating from the garage walls is a common cause of a garage door malfunctioning and getting off track.";i:36;s:41:"How to Get My Overhead Door Tracks Fixed.";i:37;s:76:"You can fix an off-track garage door by following these simple instructions.";i:38;s:33:"1 Unplug your garage door opener.";i:39;s:56:"Remember to do this before beginning any repair project.";i:40;s:78:"Disengage the opener so that you can open and close your garage door manually.";i:41;s:34:"2 Close and Lock Your Garage Door.";i:42;s:116:"The most common reason why a garage door may come off track is that you might have hit it with your car unknowingly.";i:43;s:174:"There may be days that you are rushing for work and you try to exit your vehicle even when the door has not fully opened yet causing you to hit the garage door with your car.";i:44;s:121:"If a cable breaks or becomes loose the garage door is not going to move or it is going to crash down from an up position.";i:45;s:93:"The door can also go off of its track if it isnt already off of the track for another reason.";i:46;s:65:"If a cable is too tight the door isnt going to close all the way.";i:47;s:102:"This can be a major inconvenience because you may not be able to get your car in or out of the garage.";i:48;s:53:"Broken cables and doors that are not on their tracks.";i:49;s:60:"If youre looking for an easy DIY then this might be for you.";i:50;s:76:"You may have a Chamberlain LiftMaster garage door opener with a broken belt.";i:51;s:15:"Its super easy.";i:52;s:93:"Below are some simple instructions so you know exactly how to quickly reset your garage door.";i:53;s:30:"Door Must Be in Down Position.";i:54;s:115:"Before you disengage your garage door opener from your garage door make sure that the door is in the down position.";i:55;s:76:"Attempting to disengage your door in the up position is extremely dangerous.";i:56;s:126:"My garage door was forced open and the upper rollers on the left side came off track and the cable on the right side came off.";i:57;s:115:"I was able to find videos to fix each of these issues individually but not together and I am unsure where to start.";i:58;s:24:"Any help is appreciated.";i:59;s:123:"Yes it is possible but it is critical to look at the cause of the off track and damage that may have been done to the door.";i:60;s:313:"Typically repairing a rolling door off track requires removing the track guides with the door in the fully open position and realigning the door in the track guide or guides and then re-adjusting the spring once the door is back in the track guides properly and of course reattaching the track guides to the door.";}}